  m_text: Initiative is how characters determine what order they take their turns
    during combat. When combat starts, all characters roll 1d20 and add their initiative
    modifier (their Dexterity modifier, by default). Characters act in descending
    order of their total result rolled. A character with higher Dexterity is more
    likely to act sooner during a combat scenario, as they are generally quicker
    on their feet.
